CSL Citation Styles — Attribution
==================================

The .csl style files bundled in ./styles/ are Citation Style Language (CSL) styles from the
Citation Style Language project:

    https://citationstyles.org/
    https://github.com/citation-style-language/styles

These styles are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 License
(CC-BY-SA 3.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

Bundled styles (unmodified unless noted):

    apa.csl                          APA (7th edition)
    ieee.csl                         IEEE
    chicago-author-date.csl          Chicago (author-date)  — MODIFIED: removed the
                                     page-range-format="chicago-16" attribute, which is not
                                     supported by citeproc-py 0.9.3 and raised on paginated
                                     items. Removal only changes page-range collapsing.
    modern-language-association.csl  MLA (9th edition)
    harvard-cite-them-right.csl      Harvard (Cite Them Right)
    vancouver.csl                    Vancouver
    nature.csl                       Nature

Rendering is performed by citeproc-py (https://github.com/citeproc-py/citeproc-py), which also
provides the bundled en-US locale used at render time.

Because these files are CC-BY-SA 3.0, any redistributed modifications must be shared under the
same license. See the <info>/<rights> block inside each .csl file for its per-style notice.
